text:
1. Start running towards the takeoff board.
2. Build up speed and momentum.
3. Plant the takeoff foot on the board.
4. Propel the body forward using the takeoff foot.
5. Extend the arms forward for balance.
6. Swing the non-takeoff leg forward.
7. Bring the non-takeoff leg forward and upward.
8. Extend the body horizontally in mid-air.
9. Prepare for landing by flexing the legs.
10. Land on the sandpit with the feet first.
11. Maintain balance and stability upon landing.
